				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: EQ - GONE!<a name="7704"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 30 03 2:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">If your parents have a hang up on MMORPG's being evil, tell them that you are going out this Friday to a party where beer, pot, a little Meth (but you won't try that yet), and sex all over will be involved and that you are over the obvious evil's that EQ has brought to your life.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
If his parents won't let him play EQ because it's evil, then I'd have to say it would probably be really hard for him to make his way to a party with a foot up his @$$ <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Hehe, sarcasm recognized, and aside.....making idle threats to your parents will just confirm their beliefs, not contradict them.
<br />

<br />
Remember, if they think EQ (and other fantasy-related things) is evil, then they are EXPECTING a spiritual battle for your soul.  In their opinion, the devil is going to do everything in his power to bring you over to the &quot;dark side&quot;, so to speak.  They're expecting a battle.
<br />

<br />
You need to &quot;attack from the flanks&quot;, so to speak.  Give them the exact opposite of what they're expecting and they'll more easily see that your moral compass is not going to be jeapordized, or easily swayed, by a fantasy game/book.  It will also demonstrate a level of maturity that they are probably not expecting.  That's a good thing.
<br />

<br />
A child makes idle threats.  Make idle threats and you just prove their point:  &quot;You're a child who cannot be expected to make proper decisions.&quot;  The more you act like an adult, the harder it will be for them to treat you like a child.  On the other hand, the more you act like a child, the harder it will be for them to treat you like an adult.</span></td>
